The 'Panhellenic Socialist Movement' (, ), known mostly by its acronym
'PA.SO.K.' (, pronounced ), is a centre-left party.

It was founded on 3 September 1974 by Andreas Papandreou. In 1981 the PA.SO.K. became Greece's first social democratic
party to win a majority in the Hellenic Parliament.

It is a member of the Socialist International, the Progressive Alliance of
Socialists and Democrats and the Party of European Socialists.
